# Theme Settings Import/Export Synchronization

- Any time a theme setting field is added, renamed, removed, or updated, the import/export flow must be updated in the same change.
- Import and export must remain schema-aware and compatible with the current settings structure.
- Do not ship settings changes if export output or import mapping still reflects an older field set.

## Required Actions on Field Changes

- Update export payload generation to include the latest setting fields.
- Update import parsing and mapping to handle the latest setting fields.
- Add safe defaults and fallback behavior for missing or legacy fields during import.
- Preserve backward compatibility for previously exported files when possible.
- If backward compatibility is not possible, document migration behavior clearly.

## Validation Checklist

- Confirm a newly added field appears in exported data.
- Confirm an updated field imports correctly with the new format.
- Confirm legacy export files still import safely (or fail with a clear, non-breaking message).
- Confirm no PHP notices, warnings, or fatal errors are introduced by import/export changes.

## Implementation Note

- Keep a single source of truth for settings schema (or field registry) and reuse it for UI field rendering, export construction, and import mapping to reduce drift.
